160
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:53,120
I'll turn off the lights.

161
00:13:01,140 --> 00:13:02,800
I don't get it.

162
00:13:02,800 --> 00:13:04,380
What kind of light is this?

163
00:13:04,380 --> 00:13:06,260
It can't be captured by the camera.

164
00:13:06,260 --> 00:13:08,260
And it's not the same as last time.

165
00:13:08,260 --> 00:13:10,980
It's got strokes, like a painting.

166
00:13:10,980 --> 00:13:14,360
Does the painting mean anything?

167
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:16,520
I'll get a pen.

168
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:54,340
I've done drawing.

169
00:14:00,640 --> 00:14:02,740
It's finally done.

170
00:14:04,440 --> 00:14:06,600
How's the drawing?

171
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:08,820
Well...

172
00:14:08,820 --> 00:14:10,980
So, you spent the whole night and this is what you drew?

173
00:14:10,980 --> 00:14:12,420
Hey, what do you mean?

174
00:14:12,420 --> 00:14:14,380
I was drawing without the lights.

175
00:14:14,380 --> 00:14:15,380
I couldn't even see the paper.

176
00:14:15,380 --> 00:14:17,880
